См. определение в файле symboltype.h строка 7

8 {
9  ESYMBOLTYPE_NONE=0,
10  ESYMBOLTYPE_INTEGER,
11  ESYMBOLTYPE_FLOAT,
12  ESYMBOLTYPE_STRING,
13  ESYMBOLTYPE_LOCALSTRING,
14  ESYMBOLTYPE_PAIR,
15  ESYMBOLTYPE_VECTOR,
16  ESYMBOLTYPE_QSCRIPT,
17  ESYMBOLTYPE_CFUNCTION,
18  ESYMBOLTYPE_MEMBERFUNCTION,
19  ESYMBOLTYPE_STRUCTURE,
20  // ESYMBOLTYPE_STRUCTUREPOINTER is not really used any more. It is only supported as a valid
21  // type that can be sent to AddComponent, which is an old CStruct member function that is
22  // still supported for back compatibility. mType will never be ESYMBOLTYPE_STRUCTUREPOINTER
23  ESYMBOLTYPE_STRUCTUREPOINTER,
24  ESYMBOLTYPE_ARRAY,
25  ESYMBOLTYPE_NAME,
26 
27  // These symbols are just used for memory optimization by the
28  // CScriptStructure WriteToBuffer and ReadFromBuffer functions.
29  ESYMBOLTYPE_INTEGER_ONE_BYTE,
30  ESYMBOLTYPE_INTEGER_TWO_BYTES,
31  ESYMBOLTYPE_UNSIGNED_INTEGER_ONE_BYTE,
32  ESYMBOLTYPE_UNSIGNED_INTEGER_TWO_BYTES,
33  ESYMBOLTYPE_ZERO_INTEGER,
34  ESYMBOLTYPE_ZERO_FLOAT,
35 
36  // Warning! Don't exceed 256 entries, since Type is a uint8 in SSymbolTableEntry
37  // New warning! Don't exceed 64 entries, because the top two bits of the symbol
38  // type are used to indicate whether the name checksum has been compressed to
39  // a 8 or 16 bit index, when WriteToBuffer writes out parameter names.
40 };

◆ AddChecksumName()

void Script::AddChecksumName ( uint32  checksum,
const char *  p_name 
)

См. определение в файле checksum.cpp строка 152

153 {
154  if (!Config::GotExtraMemory())
155  {
156  return;
157  }
158 
159  Dbg_MsgAssert(checksum,("Zero checksum sent to AddChecksumName"));
160  Dbg_MsgAssert(p_name,("NULL p_name sent to AddChecksumName"));
161  Dbg_MsgAssert(sp_checksum_name_hash_table,("NULL sp_checksum_name_hash_table"));
162 
163  SChecksumName *p_first=&sp_checksum_name_hash_table[(checksum&((1<<CHECKSUM_LOOKUP_HASH_BITS)-1))*CHECKSUM_ENTRIES_PER_SLOT];
164  int c=0;
165  while (p_first->mpName)
166  {
167  // Already a name here.
168  // See if it has the same checksum.
169  if (p_first->mChecksum==checksum)
170  {
171  // It does! Check whether it is the same name.
172  if (stricmp(p_first->mpName,p_name)==0)
173  {
174  // Phew, the name matches. No need to do anything.
175  return;
176  }
177  else
178  {
179  // Oh bugger, a checksum clash.
180  #ifdef __PLAT_WN32__
181  #ifdef __QDEBUG__
182  char p_foo[1024];
183  sprintf(p_foo,"Checksum clash between %s and %s, both have checksum 0x%08x",p_name,p_first->mpName,checksum);
184  MessageBox(NULL,p_foo,"Warning",MB_OK);
185  #endif
186  // Carry on anyway, won't cause a crash.
187  #else
188  Dbg_MsgAssert(0,("Checksum clash between %s and %s, both have checksum 0x%08x",p_name,p_first->mpName,checksum));
189  #endif
190  return;
191  }
192  }
193 
194  // Not the same checksum. Onto the next entry.
195  ++c;
196  Dbg_MsgAssert(c<CHECKSUM_ENTRIES_PER_SLOT,("Need to increase CHECKSUM_ENTRIES_PER_SLOT in checksum.cpp"));
197  ++p_first;
198  }
199 
200  //++sNumChecksums;
201  //printf("sNumChecksums=%d\n",sNumChecksums);
202 
203  p_first->mChecksum=checksum;
204  p_first->mpName=sp_end_of_checksum_names;
205 
206  int space_left=CHECKSUM_NAME_SPACE-(sp_end_of_checksum_names-sp_checksum_names);
207  while (*p_name)
208  {
209  Dbg_MsgAssert(space_left>0,("Need to increase CHECKSUM_NAME_SPACE in checksum.cpp"));
210  *sp_end_of_checksum_names++=*p_name++;
211  --space_left;
212  }
213  Dbg_MsgAssert(space_left>0,("Need to increase CHECKSUM_NAME_SPACE in checksum.cpp"));
214  *sp_end_of_checksum_names++=0;
215 }

Перекрестные ссылки Config::GotExtraMemory(), Script::SChecksumName::mChecksum, Script::SChecksumName::mpName, sp_checksum_name_hash_table, sp_checksum_names, sp_end_of_checksum_names и Dbg::sprintf().

Используется в ParseQB(), RegisterCFunctions() и RegisterMemberFunctions().

◆ restart_dirty_scripts()

void Script::restart_dirty_scripts ( )

См. определение в файле file.cpp строка 26

27 {
28  // For each symbol, check if it got reloaded by the above load, and if it did and it is a script
29  // then run through all the existing CScript's restarting those that referred to it.
30  // This is essential, because otherwise those CScripts' program counter pointers will now be invalid.
31  CSymbolTableEntry *p_sym=GetNextSymbolTableEntry();
32  while (p_sym)
33  {
34  if (p_sym->mGotReloaded && p_sym->mType==ESYMBOLTYPE_QSCRIPT)
35  {
36  CScript *p_script=GetNextScript();
37  while (p_script)
38  {
39  if (p_script->RefersToScript(p_sym->mNameChecksum))
40  {
41  p_script->Restart();
42  }
43 
44  p_script=GetNextScript(p_script);
45  }
46 
47  // Reset the reloaded flag, otherwise it will stick on forever.
48  p_sym->mGotReloaded=false;
49  }
50  p_sym=GetNextSymbolTableEntry(p_sym);
51  }
52 }

◆ UnloadQB()

void Script::UnloadQB ( uint32  fileNameChecksum)

См. определение в файле file.cpp строка 106

107 {
108  // Do nothing if the checksum is zero. This is essential, because symbols
109  // that have a mSourceFileNameChecksum of 0 are those that did not come
110  // from a qb file, ie C-functions. These must never be deleted.
111  if (!fileNameChecksum)
112  {
113  return;
114  }
115 
116  // Scan through all the symbols in the symbol table.
117  CSymbolTableEntry *p_sym=GetNextSymbolTableEntry();
118  while (p_sym)
119  {
120  if (p_sym->mSourceFileNameChecksum==fileNameChecksum)
121  {
122  // This symbol was defined in the passed qb file, so remove it.
123  CleanUpAndRemoveSymbol(p_sym);
124  // Need to start checking from the start of the list again rather than storing
125  // a p_next pointer before calling CleanUpAndRemoveSymbol.
126  // This is because CleanUpAndRemoveSymbol may cause the symbol above to move down,
127  // invalidating p_next.
128  // SPEEDOPT Starting again from the start of the list is inefficient though, because
129  // it may have to scan through thousands of symbols just to delete one, and may have to
130  // delete say a hundred. Optimize later. (Seems fast enough at the moment)
131  p_sym=NULL;
132  }
133  p_sym=GetNextSymbolTableEntry(p_sym);
134  }
135 
136  // Scan through all the existing CScripts stopping any that are referring to a script
137  // that got deleted above.
138  CScript *p_script=GetNextScript();
139  while (p_script)
140  {
141  if (!p_script->AllScriptsInCallstackStillExist())
142  {
143  p_script->ClearScript();
144  p_script->ClearEventHandlerTable();
145  }
146 
147  p_script=GetNextScript(p_script);
148  }
149 }

Перекрестные ссылки CleanUpAndRemoveSymbol(), GetNextScript(), GetNextSymbolTableEntry(), Script::CSymbolTableEntry::mSourceFileNameChecksum и p_script.

Используется в SkateScript::UnloadQB().

◆ sCalculateRandomRange()

static uint8 * Script::sCalculateRandomRange ( uint8 *  p_token,
CComponent *  p_comp,
bool  useRnd2 
)
static

См. определение в файле parse.cpp строка 176

177 {
178  // RandomRange token must be followed by a pair.
179  Dbg_MsgAssert(*p_token==ESCRIPTTOKEN_PAIR,("RandomRange operator must be followed by a pair of values in parentheses, File %s, line %d",GetSourceFile(p_token),GetLineNumber(p_token)));
180  ++p_token;
181  // Get the range values, which are floats cos it's a pair.
182  float x=Read4Bytes(p_token).mFloat;
183  p_token+=4;
184  float y=Read4Bytes(p_token).mFloat;
185  p_token+=4;
186 
187  // Get the integer values.
188  // Offset the floats up or down by 0.01 to ensure they round down to the expected integer values.
189  int a, b;
190  a=(int)( (x<0) ? x-0.1f:x+0.1f);
191  b=(int)( (y<0) ? y-0.1f:y+0.1f);
192 
193  bool they_are_integers=true;
194  if (fabs(x-a) > 0.00001f || fabs(y-b) > 0.00001f)
195  {
196  they_are_integers=false;
197  }
198 
199  if (they_are_integers)
200  {
201  // Make sure that a<=b
202  if (a>b)
203  {
204  // Swap them.
205  int temp=a;
206  a=b;
207  b=temp;
208  }
209  // Get val, which is between a and b inclusive.
210  // This assert is to make sure the calculations in Rnd don't overflow.
211  Dbg_MsgAssert(b-a+1<=32767,("File %s, line %d: RandomRange limits are too far apart, max is 32767",GetSourceFile(p_token),GetLineNumber(p_token)));
212  int val;
213  if (useRnd2)
214  {
215  val=a+Mth::Rnd2(b-a+1);
216  }
217  else
218  {
219  val=a+Mth::Rnd(b-a+1);
220  }
221  // Make totally sure the value is OK, cos could lead to hard-to-track-down bugs otherwise.
222 // Dbg_MsgAssert(val>=a && val<=b,("File %s, line %d: Internal error in RandomRange (%f %f %f), fire Ken.",GetSourceFile(p_token),GetLineNumber(p_token),x,y,val));
223 
224  p_comp->mType=ESYMBOLTYPE_INTEGER;
225  p_comp->mIntegerValue=val;
226  }
227  else
228  {
229  // Make sure that x<=y
230  if (x>y)
231  {
232  // Swap them.
233  float temp=x;
234  x=y;
235  y=temp;
236  }
237  // Get val, which is between x and y inclusive.
238  float val;
239  // Don't make FLOAT_RES bigger than 32766 because the calculations in Rnd will overflow otherwise.
240  #define FLOAT_RES 32760.0f
241  if (useRnd2)
242  {
243  val=x+((float)Mth::Rnd2((int)(FLOAT_RES+1.0f))*(y-x))/FLOAT_RES;
244  }
245  else
246  {
247  val=x+((float)Mth::Rnd((int)(FLOAT_RES+1.0f))*(y-x))/FLOAT_RES;
248  }
249 
250  // Make totally sure the value is OK, cos could lead to hard-to-track-down bugs otherwise.
251 // Dbg_MsgAssert(val>=x && val<=y,("File %s, line %d: Internal error in RandomRange (%f %f %f), fire Ken.",GetSourceFile(p_token),GetLineNumber(p_token),x,y,val));
252 
253  p_comp->mType=ESYMBOLTYPE_FLOAT;
254  p_comp->mFloatValue=val;
255  }
256 
257  return p_token;
258 }

Перекрестные ссылки ESCRIPTTOKEN_PAIR, ESYMBOLTYPE_FLOAT, ESYMBOLTYPE_INTEGER, fabs(), GetLineNumber(), GetSourceFile(), Script::S4Bytes::mFloat, Script::CComponent::mFloatValue, Script::CComponent::mIntegerValue, Script::CComponent::mType, Read4Bytes(), Mth::Rnd(), Mth::Rnd2(), x и Nx::y.

◆ sSkipType()

static uint8 * Script::sSkipType ( uint8 *  p_token)

См. определение в файле parse.cpp строка 262

263 {
264  switch (*p_token)
265  {
266  case ESCRIPTTOKEN_NAME:
267  case ESCRIPTTOKEN_INTEGER:
268  case ESCRIPTTOKEN_HEXINTEGER:

280  p_token+=1+4+Read4Bytes(p_token+1).mUInt;
281  break;
282  case ESCRIPTTOKEN_STARTSTRUCT:
283  {
284  int StructCount=1;
285  while (StructCount)
286  {
287  p_token=SkipToken(p_token);
288  if (*p_token==ESCRIPTTOKEN_STARTSTRUCT)
289  {
290  ++StructCount;
291  }
292  else if (*p_token==ESCRIPTTOKEN_ENDSTRUCT)
293  {
294  --StructCount;
295  }
296  }
297  ++p_token;
298  break;
299  }
300  case ESCRIPTTOKEN_STARTARRAY:
301  {
302  int ArrayCount=1;
303  while (ArrayCount)
304  {
305  p_token=SkipToken(p_token);
306  if (*p_token==ESCRIPTTOKEN_STARTARRAY)
307  {
308  ++ArrayCount;
309  }
310  else if (*p_token==ESCRIPTTOKEN_ENDARRAY)
311  {
312  --ArrayCount;
313  }
314  }
315  ++p_token;
316  break;
317  }
318  default:
319  Dbg_MsgAssert(0,("Unrecognized type"));
320  break;
321  }
322  return p_token;
323 }

Перекрестные ссылки ESCRIPTTOKEN_ENDARRAY, ESCRIPTTOKEN_ENDSTRUCT, ESCRIPTTOKEN_FLOAT, ESCRIPTTOKEN_HEXINTEGER, ESCRIPTTOKEN_INTEGER, ESCRIPTTOKEN_LOCALSTRING, ESCRIPTTOKEN_NAME, ESCRIPTTOKEN_PAIR, ESCRIPTTOKEN_STARTARRAY, ESCRIPTTOKEN_STARTSTRUCT, ESCRIPTTOKEN_STRING, ESCRIPTTOKEN_VECTOR, Script::S4Bytes::mUInt, Read4Bytes() и SkipToken().

Используется в sInitArrayFromQB().

1380  // Note: This used to be after the switch statement below. Moved it here so that if any
1381  // assert goes off in the switch statement the file name info will be present in the symbol.
1382  p_new->mSourceFileNameChecksum=Crc::GenerateCRCFromString(p_fileName);
1383 
1384  // Now see what type of value follows the equals, and fill in the new symbol accordingly.
1385  switch (*p_token)
1386  {
1387  case ESCRIPTTOKEN_OPENPARENTH:
1388  {
1389  CComponent *p_comp=new CComponent;
1390  p_token=Evaluate(p_token,NULL,p_comp);
1391  Dbg_MsgAssert(p_comp->mType!=ESYMBOLTYPE_NONE,("Global symbol '%s' did not evaluate to anything ...",FindChecksumName(p_comp->mNameChecksum)));
1392  p_new->mType=p_comp->mType;
1393  p_new->mUnion=p_comp->mUnion;
1394  p_comp->mUnion=0;
1395  delete p_comp;
1396  break;
1397  }
1398 
1399  case ESCRIPTTOKEN_INTEGER:
1400  case ESCRIPTTOKEN_FLOAT:
1401  case ESCRIPTTOKEN_VECTOR:
1402  case ESCRIPTTOKEN_PAIR:
1403  case ESCRIPTTOKEN_STRING:
1404  case ESCRIPTTOKEN_LOCALSTRING:
1405  case ESCRIPTTOKEN_NAME:
1406  {
1407  CComponent *p_comp=new CComponent;
1408  p_token=FillInComponentUsingQB(p_token,NULL,p_comp);
1409  p_new->mType=p_comp->mType;
1410  p_new->mUnion=p_comp->mUnion;
1411  p_comp->mUnion=0;
1412  delete p_comp;
1413  break;
1414  }
1415 
1416  case ESCRIPTTOKEN_STARTSTRUCT:
1417  {
1418  p_new->mType=ESYMBOLTYPE_STRUCTURE;
1419  p_new->mpStructure=new CStruct;
1420 
1421  p_token=sAddComponentsWithinCurlyBraces(p_new->mpStructure,p_token);
1422  break;
1423  }
1424  case ESCRIPTTOKEN_STARTARRAY:
1425  {
1426  p_new->mType=ESYMBOLTYPE_ARRAY;
1427 
1428  p_new->mpArray=new CArray;
1429  p_token=sInitArrayFromQB(p_new->mpArray,p_token);
1430  break;
1431  }
1432 
1433  default:
1434  Dbg_MsgAssert(0,("\nUnexpected type value of %d given to symbol '%s', line %d of %s",*p_token,FindChecksumName(name_checksum),GetLineNumber(p_token),p_fileName));
1435  break;
1436  } // switch (*p_token)
1437 
1438  return p_token;
1439 }

1808 
1809  p_stored->mCurrentIndex=0;
1810  Dbg_MsgAssert(num_items<=MAX_RANDOM_INDICES,("Too many entries in RandomPermute, max is %d. Line %d of file %s",MAX_RANDOM_INDICES,GetLineNumber(p_token),GetSourceFile(p_token)));
1811 
1812  p_stored->InitIndices();
1813  p_stored->RandomizeIndices();
1814  }
1815  p_stored->mpScript=GetCurrentScript();
1816 
1817  ++p_stored->mCurrentIndex;
1818  if (p_stored->mCurrentIndex>=p_stored->mNumItems)
1819  {
1820  p_stored->RandomizeIndices(MAKE_NEW_FIRST_DIFFER_FROM_OLD_LAST);
1821  p_stored->mCurrentIndex=0;
1822  }
1823  uint16 jump_index=p_stored->mpIndices[p_stored->mCurrentIndex];
1824  Dbg_MsgAssert(jump_index<num_items,("Eh? jump_index out of range ?"));
1825 
1826  p_token+=4*jump_index; // Jump to the offset
1827  sint32 offset=Read4Bytes(p_token).mInt; // Get the offset
1828  p_token+=4; // Skip over the offset
1829  p_token+=offset; // Jump to the item
1830  break;
1831  }
1832  case ESCRIPTTOKEN_JUMP:
1833  {
1834  ++p_token; // Skip over the jump token.
1835  sint32 offset=Read4Bytes(p_token).mInt;
1836  p_token+=4; // Skip over the offset
1837  p_token+=offset; // Do the jump
1838  break;
1839  }
1840  default:
1841  finished=true;
1842  break;
1843  }
1844 
1845  if (finished)
1846  {
1847  break;
1848  }
1849  }
1850  return p_token;
1851 }

2816  break;
2817

2819  {

2823  p_token=Evaluate(p_token,p_args,p_comp);
2824 
2825  if (p_comp->mType==ESYMBOLTYPE_STRUCTURE)
2826  {
2827  // The CStruct::AddComponent function does not allow unnamed structure
2828  // components to be added, so merge in the contents of the structure instead.
2829  p_dest->AppendStructure(p_comp->mpStructure);
2830  // Now p_comp does have to be cleaned up and deleted, because it has not
2831  // been given to p_dest.
2832  CleanUpComponent(p_comp);
2833  delete p_comp;
2834  }
2835  else
2836  {

2838  {

2840  p_dest->AddComponent(p_comp);
2841  }
2842  else
2843  {
2844  delete p_comp;
2845  }
2846  }
2847  }
2848  else
2849  {
2850  p_token=sAddComponentFromQB(p_dest,NO_NAME,p_token,p_args);
2851  }
2852  break;
2853  }
2854  }
2855  }
2856 
2857  // Note: Does not skip over the end-of-lines. This is so that if any asserts go off during the
2858  // C-function or member function call that this structure is going to be used as parameters too,
2859  // the assert will print the correct line number, rather than the one following.
2860  return p_token;

3300  // No symbol currently exists with this name, so create the new script symbol.
3301  sCreateScriptSymbol(name_checksum,new_contents_checksum,p_script_data,script_data_size,p_fileName);
3302  }
3303  break;
3304  }
3305

3307  // These have been done already, so skip over.
3308  p_token=SkipToken(p_token);
3309  break;

3312  end_of_file=true;
3313  break;
3314 
3315  default:
3316  Dbg_MsgAssert(0,("\nConfused by line %d of %s.\nExpected either a script definition (Script ... EndScript)\nor a constant definition (Something=...)",GetLineNumber(p_token),p_fileName));
3317  break;

3319  }
3320

3322  s_qb_being_parsed=0;

3011  printf("Warning! RunScript sent '%s' which is not a script, a c-function or a member function. Type=%s\n",sGetRunScriptName(scriptChecksum,p_scriptName),GetTypeName(p_entry->mType));
3012  #endif
3013  return;
3014  }
3015 
3016 
3017  if( netScript )
3018  {
3019  SendScript( scriptChecksum, p_params, p_object );
3020  }
3021 
3022  switch (p_entry->mType)
3023  {
3024  case ESYMBOLTYPE_CFUNCTION:
3025  {
3026  // If the symbol is actually a c-function rather than a script, then run the c-function.
3027  // This is handy sometimes because it saves having to write a special script just to run
3028  // one c-function.
3029  Dbg_MsgAssert(p_entry->mpCFunction,("NULL pCFunction"));
3030 
3031  // Mick: We now pass in NULL, as creating a dummy script is very slow
3032  (*p_entry->mpCFunction)(p_params,NULL);
3033 
3034  break;
3035  }
3036 
3037  case ESYMBOLTYPE_MEMBERFUNCTION:
3038  {
3039  Dbg_MsgAssert(p_object,("Tried to run member function '%s' on NULL p_object",Script::FindChecksumName(scriptChecksum)));
3040 
3041  // Mick: We now pass in NULL, as creating a dummy script is very slow
3042  p_object->CallMemberFunction(scriptChecksum,p_params,NULL);
3043 
3044  break;
3045  }
3046 
3047  case ESYMBOLTYPE_QSCRIPT:
3048  {
3049  Mem::Manager::sHandle().PushContext(Mem::Manager::sHandle().ScriptHeap());
3050  CScript *p_script=new CScript;
3051  #ifdef __NOPT_ASSERT__
3052  p_script->SetCommentString("Created by RunScript(...)");
3053  #endif
3054  p_script->SetScript(scriptChecksum,p_params,p_object);
3055  Mem::Manager::sHandle().PopContext();
3056 
3057  while (true)
3058  {
3059  EScriptReturnVal ret_val=p_script->Update();
3060  if (ret_val==ESCRIPTRETURNVAL_FINISHED)
3061  {
3062  break;
3063  }
3064  //Dbg_MsgAssert(0,("\n%s\nScript did not finish when run by RunScript.",p_script->GetScriptInfo()));
3065  // Script must not get blocked, otherwise it'll hang in this loop forever.
3066  Dbg_MsgAssert(ret_val!=ESCRIPTRETURNVAL_BLOCKED,("\n%s\nScript got blocked when being run by RunScript.",p_script->GetScriptInfo()));
3067  // Note: OK if the script returns ESCRIPTRETURNVAL_WAITING, because the wait period will eventually end.
3068 
3069  }
3070  delete p_script;
3071  break;
3072  }
3073 
3074  default:
3075  break;
3076  }
3077 }

◆ sAddToSpecialStringHeap()

static char * Script::sAddToSpecialStringHeap ( const char *  p_string)
static

См. определение в файле string.cpp строка 96

97 {
98  Dbg_MsgAssert(p_string,("NULL p_string"));
99 
100  // Check to see if it already exists in the special string heap ...
101 
102  // Calculate the checksum of the string, then search for this in the array of
103  // checksums of all the special strings so far.
104  // Quicker than doing byte comparisons, probably due to the long time it takes to
105  // read single bytes from memory.
106  // Needs to be fast, otherwise it can add a significant delay to the startup time.
107  // This method adds about 0.3 seconds altogether (in THPS3, couple of thousand strings)
108  uint32 len=strlen(p_string);
109  uint32 checksum=Crc::GenerateCRCCaseSensitive(p_string,len);
110 
111  Dbg_MsgAssert(sp_permanent_string_checksums,("NULL sp_permanent_string_checksums ??"));
112  SSpecialStringChecksum *p_ch=sp_permanent_string_checksums;
113  for (uint32 i=0; i<s_num_permanent_string_checksums; ++i)
114  {
115  if (p_ch->mChecksum==checksum)
116  {
117  return p_ch->mpString;
118  }
119  ++p_ch;
120  }
121 
122  char *p_heap_string=NULL;
123 
124  // Not found, so add to the pile of strings.
125  Dbg_MsgAssert(sp_permanent_string_heap,("NULL sp_permanent_string_heap ??"));
126 
127  Dbg_MsgAssert(s_permanent_string_heap_size-(sp_permanent_string_heap_top-sp_permanent_string_heap)>=len+1,("Out of special string heap"));
128  p_heap_string=sp_permanent_string_heap_top;
129  strcpy(p_heap_string,p_string);
130  // Update sp_permanent_string_heap_top
131  sp_permanent_string_heap_top+=len;
132  ++sp_permanent_string_heap_top; // Skip over the terminator
133 
134  // Store the checksum too.
135  Dbg_MsgAssert(s_num_permanent_string_checksums<s_max_permanent_string_checksums,("Ran out of permanent-string checksums"));
136  sp_permanent_string_checksums[s_num_permanent_string_checksums].mChecksum=checksum;
137  sp_permanent_string_checksums[s_num_permanent_string_checksums].mpString=p_heap_string;
138  ++s_num_permanent_string_checksums;
139

◆ UseRegularStringHeap()

void Script::UseRegularStringHeap ( )

См. определение в файле string.cpp строка 148

149 {
150  s_use_permanent_string_heap=false;
151 
152  // 56K memory saving, though this assumes that UsePermanentStringHeap() won't be called
153  // again after UseRegularStringHeap(). If it is, the code will assert as soon as a string
154  // is attempted to be created.
155  // The current code does not use the permanent string heap again, so use the savings.
156  // (End of THPS6 and memory is tight)
157  if (sp_permanent_string_checksums)
158  {
159  Mem::Free(sp_permanent_string_checksums);
160  sp_permanent_string_checksums=NULL;
161  }
162 }

Перекрестные ссылки Mem::Free(), s_use_permanent_string_heap и sp_permanent_string_checksums.

◆ CleanUpComponent()

void Script::CleanUpComponent ( CComponent *  p_comp)

См. определение в файле struct.cpp строка 56

57 {
58  Dbg_MsgAssert(p_comp,("NULL p_comp"));
59 
60  switch (p_comp->mType)
61  {
62  case ESYMBOLTYPE_STRING:
63  case ESYMBOLTYPE_LOCALSTRING:
64  if (p_comp->mpString)
65  {
66  DeleteString(p_comp->mpString);
67  }
68  break;
69  case ESYMBOLTYPE_PAIR:
70  if (p_comp->mpPair)
71  {
72  delete p_comp->mpPair;
73  }
74  break;
75  case ESYMBOLTYPE_VECTOR:
76  if (p_comp->mpVector)
77  {
78  delete p_comp->mpVector;
79  }
80  break;
81  case ESYMBOLTYPE_STRUCTURE:
82  if (p_comp->mpStructure)
83  {
84  delete p_comp->mpStructure;
85  }
86  break;
87  case ESYMBOLTYPE_ARRAY:
88  if (p_comp->mpArray)
89  {
90  CleanUpArray(p_comp->mpArray);
91  delete p_comp->mpArray;
92  }
93  break;
94  case ESYMBOLTYPE_QSCRIPT:
95  if (p_comp->mpScript)
96  {
97  Mem::Free(p_comp->mpScript);
98  }
99  p_comp->mScriptSize=0;
100  break;
101  default:
102  break;
103  }
104  // This will zero the union, which includes all the above pointers.
105  p_comp->mUnion=0;
106 
107  p_comp->mType=ESYMBOLTYPE_NONE;
108 }

113 {

129  break;
130

132  case ESYMBOLTYPE_FLOAT:
133  case ESYMBOLTYPE_NAME:
134  p_dest->mUnion=p_source->mUnion;
135  break;
136 
137  case ESYMBOLTYPE_STRING:
138  Dbg_MsgAssert(p_source->mpString,("NULL p_source->mpString ?"));

160  break;
161 
162  case ESYMBOLTYPE_STRUCTURE:
163  Dbg_MsgAssert(p_source->mpStructure,("NULL p_source->mpStructure ?"));
164  p_dest->mpStructure=new CStruct;
165  *p_dest->mpStructure=*p_source->mpStructure;
166  break;

169  Dbg_MsgAssert(p_source->mpArray,("NULL p_source->mpArray ?"));
170  p_dest->mpArray=new CArray;
171  CopyArray(p_dest->mpArray,p_source->mpArray);
172  break;
173 
174  case ESYMBOLTYPE_QSCRIPT:
175  {
176  Dbg_MsgAssert(p_source->mpScript,("NULL p_source->mpScript ?"));
177 
178  // Allocate a buffer off the script heap
179  Mem::Manager::sHandle().PushContext(Mem::Manager::sHandle().ScriptHeap());
180  Dbg_MsgAssert(p_source->mScriptSize,("Zero source script size"));
181  p_dest->mpScript=(uint8*)Mem::Malloc(p_source->mScriptSize);
182  p_dest->mScriptSize=p_source->mScriptSize;
183  Mem::Manager::sHandle().PopContext();
184 
185  // Copy the script into the new buffer.
186  const uint8 *p_from=p_source->mpScript;
187  uint8 *p_to=p_dest->mpScript;
188  for (uint32 i=0; i<p_source->mScriptSize; ++i)
189  {
190  *p_to++=*p_from++;
191  }
192 
193  break;
194  }
195 
196  default:
197  Dbg_MsgAssert(0,("Bad p_source->mType of '%s'",GetTypeName(p_source->mType)));
198  break;
199  }
200 }

◆ CopyArray()

void Script::CopyArray ( CArray *  p_dest,

)

См. определение в файле struct.cpp строка 314

315 {
316  Dbg_MsgAssert(p_source,("NULL p_source ?"));
317  Dbg_MsgAssert(p_dest,("NULL p_dest ?"));
318 
319  // Make sure that p_dest is cleaned up first.
320  CleanUpArray(p_dest);
321 
322  ESymbolType type=p_source->GetType();
323  uint32 size=p_source->GetSize();
324 
325  p_dest->SetSizeAndType(size,type);
326 
327  if (size==0)
328  {
329  // Finished.
330  return;
331  }
332 
333  uint32 *p_source_array=p_source->GetArrayPointer();
334  Dbg_MsgAssert(p_source_array,("NULL p_source_array ?"));
335 
336  uint32 *p_dest_array=p_dest->GetArrayPointer();
337  Dbg_MsgAssert(p_dest_array,("NULL p_dest_array ?"));
338 
339  switch (type)
340  {
341  case ESYMBOLTYPE_INTEGER:
342  case ESYMBOLTYPE_FLOAT:
343  case ESYMBOLTYPE_NAME:
344  {
345  uint32 *p_source_word=p_source_array;
346  uint32 *p_dest_word=p_dest_array;
347  for (uint32 i=0; i<size; ++i)
348  {
349  *p_dest_word++=*p_source_word++;
350  }
351  break;
352  }
353 
354  case ESYMBOLTYPE_STRING:
355  case ESYMBOLTYPE_LOCALSTRING:
356  {
357  char **pp_source_string=(char**)p_source_array;
358  char **pp_dest_string=(char**)p_dest_array;
359  for (uint32 i=0; i<size; ++i)
360  {
361  char *p_source_string=*pp_source_string;
362  if (p_source_string)
363  {
364  // Create a new copy of the source string.
365  *pp_dest_string=CreateString(p_source_string);
366  }
367  ++pp_source_string;
368  ++pp_dest_string;
369  }
370  break;
371  }

377  for (uint32 i=0; i<size; ++i)
378  {
379  CPair *p_source_pair=*pp_source_pair;
380  if (p_source_pair)
381  {
382  CPair *p_new_pair=new CPair;
383  // The default assignement operator works OK for CPair since it contains no pointers.
384  *p_new_pair=*p_source_pair;
385  *pp_dest_pair=p_new_pair;
386  }
387  ++pp_source_pair;
388  ++pp_dest_pair;
389  }
390  break;
391  }
392

397  for (uint32 i=0; i<size; ++i)
398  {
399  CVector *p_source_vector=*pp_source_vector;
400  if (p_source_vector)
401  {
402  CVector *p_new_vector=new CVector;
403  // The default assignement operator works OK for CVector since it contains no pointers.
404  *p_new_vector=*p_source_vector;
405  *pp_dest_vector=p_new_vector;
406  }
407  ++pp_source_vector;
408  ++pp_dest_vector;
409  }
410  break;
411  }
412 
413  case ESYMBOLTYPE_STRUCTURE:
414  {
415  CStruct **pp_source_structure=(CStruct**)p_source_array;
416  CStruct **pp_dest_structure=(CStruct**)p_dest_array;
417  for (uint32 i=0; i<size; ++i)
418  {
419  CStruct *p_source_structure=*pp_source_structure;
420  if (p_source_structure)
421  {
422  CStruct *p_new_structure=new CStruct;
423  // Copy the contents using CStruct's assignement operator.
424  *p_new_structure=*p_source_structure;
425  *pp_dest_structure=p_new_structure;
426  }
427  ++pp_source_structure;
428  ++pp_dest_structure;
429  }
430  break;
431  }
432 
433  case ESYMBOLTYPE_ARRAY:
434  {
435  CArray **pp_source_carray=(CArray**)p_source_array;
436  CArray **pp_dest_carray=(CArray**)p_dest_array;
437  for (uint32 i=0; i<size; ++i)
438  {
439  CArray *p_source_carray=*pp_source_carray;
440  if (p_source_carray)
441  {
442  CArray *p_new_carray=new CArray;
443  // No assignement operator defined for CArray (cos it would cause cyclic dependencies)
444  // so need to use CopyArray.
445  CopyArray(p_new_carray,p_source_carray);
446  *pp_dest_carray=p_new_carray;
447  }
448  ++pp_source_carray;
449  ++pp_dest_carray;
450  }
451  break;
452  }
453 
454  default:
455  Dbg_MsgAssert(0,("Bad source array type of '%s'",GetTypeName(type)));
456  break;
457  }
458 }

◆ Resolve() [1/3]

CSymbolTableEntry * Script::Resolve ( uint32  checksum)

См. определение в файле symboltable.cpp строка 211

212 {
213  // Look up the checksum.
214  CSymbolTableEntry *p_entry=LookUpSymbol(checksum);
215  if (p_entry && p_entry->mType==ESYMBOLTYPE_NAME)
216  {
217  // If the symbol is of type name, then it may be that the name is the name of another symbol,
218  // in which case we need to find that.
219  // Eg we could be trying to resolve a, where a=b, b=c, c=7, in which case we need to find 7.
220  // So loop until either a non-name symbol is reached, or no further symbol is reached.
221 
222  #ifdef __NOPT_ASSERT__
223  // An infinite loop could occur, for example if we have a global a=b where b=a
224  // This counter will make an assert go off if we try and loop a suspicious number of times.
225  uint32 num_loops=0;
226  #endif
227 
228  while (true)
229  {
230  CSymbolTableEntry *p_new=LookUpSymbol(p_entry->mChecksum);
231  if (!p_new)
232  {
233  // Reached the end of the chain, so return the last entry, which will have type name.
234  return p_entry;
235  }
236 
237  if (p_new->mType!=ESYMBOLTYPE_NAME)
238  {
239  // Reached something not of type name, so return that.
240  return p_new;
241  }
242 
243  // Repeat.
244  p_entry=p_new;
245  Dbg_MsgAssert(num_loops++<10,("Possible infinite recursion of the Resolve function when trying to resolve '%s', bailing out!",FindChecksumName(checksum)));
246  }
247  }
248 
249  return p_entry;
250 }

void Script::RemoveSymbol ( CSymbolTableEntry *  p_sym)

264 {
265  Dbg_MsgAssert(p_sym,("NULL p_sym"));
266  Dbg_MsgAssert(p_sym->mUnion==0,("CSymbolTableEntry still contains data, possibly an undeleted pointer. Type='%s'",GetTypeName(p_sym->mType)));
267  Dbg_MsgAssert(p_sym->mUsed,("Tried to call RemoveSymbol on an unused CSymbolTableEntry"));
268  Dbg_MsgAssert(sp_hash_table!=NULL,("sp_hash_table is NULL ?"));
269 
270  // Get the head pointer of the list that p_sym is in (or should be in)
271  CSymbolTableEntry *p_head=&sp_hash_table[ p_sym->mNameChecksum & ((1<<NUM_HASH_BITS)-1) ];
272 
273  if (p_sym==p_head)
274  {
275  // p_sym is in the hash table itself, so it must not be deleted because it is an element of
276  // a contiguous array, not allocated off the pool.
277 
278  // Check if there are further entries in the list. These will have been allocated off the pool.
279  if (p_sym->mpNext)
280  {
281  // There are later entries in the list, so copy the first of these down
282  // to fill the hole.
283  CSymbolTableEntry *p_source=p_sym->mpNext;
284 
285  // Copy the contents. Not using the assignement operator because that won't link.
286  // It is declared but not defined so as to cause it not to link, to prevent any problems
287  // with copying pointers if it gets used anywhere else.
288  uint32 *p_source_word=(uint32*)p_source;
289  uint32 *p_dest_word=(uint32*)p_sym;
290  Dbg_MsgAssert((sizeof(CSymbolTableEntry)&3)==0,("sizeof(CSymbolTableEntry) not a multiple of 4 ?"));
291  for (uint32 i=0; i<sizeof(CSymbolTableEntry)/4; ++i)
292  {
293  *p_dest_word++=*p_source_word++;
294  }
295 
296  // Need to zero the union so that the destructor does not think there is an undeleted
297  // pointer in it, which will make it assert.
298  p_source->mUnion=0;
299  delete p_source;
300  }
301  else
302  {
303  // Just reset the contents of p_sym.
304  p_sym->Reset();
305  }
306  }
307  else
308  {
309  // p_sym is not in the hash table, so it must have been allocated off the pool.
310  // In order to unlink it from the list we need to find the previous entry in the list.
311  // So search through the list until p_sym is found.
312 
313  // Start with mpNext, cos we know p_sym is not p_head
314  CSymbolTableEntry *p_previous=p_head;
315  CSymbolTableEntry *p_search=p_head->mpNext;
316  while (p_search)
317  {
318  if (p_search==p_sym)
319  {
320  break;
321  }
322  p_previous=p_search;
323  p_search=p_search->mpNext;
324  }
325 
326  Dbg_MsgAssert(p_search,("p_sym not found in list ? (checksum='%s')",FindChecksumName(p_sym->mNameChecksum)));
327 
328  // Unlink p_sym and delete it.
329  p_previous->mpNext=p_sym->mpNext;
330  delete p_sym;
331  }
332 }

◆ GetNextSymbolTableEntry()

CSymbolTableEntry * Script::GetNextSymbolTableEntry ( CSymbolTableEntry *  p_sym)

См. определение в файле symboltable.cpp строка 405

406 {
407  // static's for keeping track of where we are in the hash table.
408  static uint32 s_current_hash_index=0;
409  static CSymbolTableEntry *sp_last=NULL;
410 
411  if (p_sym==NULL)
412  {
413  // They want the first symbol.
414  s_current_hash_index=0;
415  p_sym=sp_hash_table;
416 
417  // Step through the hash table entries until a used one is found.
418  while (!p_sym->mUsed)
419  {
420  ++s_current_hash_index;
421  ++p_sym;
422 
423  if (s_current_hash_index>=(1<<NUM_HASH_BITS))
424  {
425  // Run out of hash table.
426  s_current_hash_index=0;
427  sp_last=NULL;
428  return NULL;
429  }
430  }
431 
432  sp_last=p_sym;
433  return p_sym;
434  }
435  else
436  {
437  // Check that p_sym is the same as the last one returned by this function.
438 
439  // Currently this function assumes that the user is going to be calling it on
440  // consecutive elements, such as in the example loop given in the comment for this function.
441  // In theory it could be made to work when passed an arbitrary member of the symbol table, but this
442  // would require it to search forward from the start each time in order to find out what index the
443  // list is at.
444  // It was easier and faster to just store the index as a static and assert if called on
445  // non-consecutive symbols. (Could fix it if it becomes a problem)
446  Dbg_MsgAssert(p_sym==sp_last,("Non-consecutive call to GetNextSymbolTableEntry"));
447  }
448 
449  p_sym=p_sym->mpNext;
450  if (!p_sym)
451  {
452  // We've gone off the end of this linked list, so go onto the next entry in the hash table.
453  ++s_current_hash_index;
454  p_sym=sp_hash_table+s_current_hash_index;
455 
456  if (s_current_hash_index>=(1<<NUM_HASH_BITS))
457  {
458  // Run out of hash table.
459  s_current_hash_index=0;
460  sp_last=NULL;
461  return NULL;
462  }
463 
464  // Step through the hash table entries until a used one is found.
465  while (!p_sym->mUsed)
466  {
467  ++s_current_hash_index;
468  ++p_sym;
469 
470  if (s_current_hash_index>=(1<<NUM_HASH_BITS))
471  {
472  s_current_hash_index=0;
473  sp_last=NULL;
474  return NULL;
475  }
476  }
477  }
478 
479  sp_last=p_sym;
480  return p_sym;
481 }

315  }

331  }
332

340 {
341  uint8 *p_buffer_before=p_buffer;
342 
343  // Choose what type of symbol to use so as to minimize the space used.
344 
345  ESymbolType symbol_type=ESYMBOLTYPE_INTEGER; // Default to a full 4 bytes.
346 
347  if (val==0)
348  {
349  symbol_type=ESYMBOLTYPE_ZERO_INTEGER;
350  }
351  else if (val>=0 && val<=255)
352  {
353  symbol_type=ESYMBOLTYPE_UNSIGNED_INTEGER_ONE_BYTE;
354  }
355  else if (val>=0 && val<=65535)
356  {
357  symbol_type=ESYMBOLTYPE_UNSIGNED_INTEGER_TWO_BYTES;
358  }
359  else if (val>=-128 && val<=127)
360  {
361  symbol_type=ESYMBOLTYPE_INTEGER_ONE_BYTE;
362  }
363  else if (val>=-32768 && val<=32767)
364  {
365  symbol_type=ESYMBOLTYPE_INTEGER_TWO_BYTES;
366  }
367 
368 
369  uint8 p_temp[20];
370  uint8 *p_end=p_temp;
371 
372  switch (symbol_type)
373  {
374  case ESYMBOLTYPE_INTEGER:
375  // Write out the component into p_temp
376  p_end=sWriteCompressedName(p_temp,symbol_type,name);
377  p_end=Write4Bytes(p_end,(uint32)val);
378  break;
379 
380  case ESYMBOLTYPE_INTEGER_ONE_BYTE:
381  case ESYMBOLTYPE_UNSIGNED_INTEGER_ONE_BYTE:
382  // Write out the component into p_temp
383  p_end=sWriteCompressedName(p_temp,symbol_type,name);
384  *p_end++=(uint8)val;
385  break;
386 
387  case ESYMBOLTYPE_INTEGER_TWO_BYTES:
388  case ESYMBOLTYPE_UNSIGNED_INTEGER_TWO_BYTES:
389  // Write out the component.
390  p_end=sWriteCompressedName(p_temp,symbol_type,name);
391  p_end=Write2Bytes(p_end,(uint16)val);
392  break;
393 
394  case ESYMBOLTYPE_ZERO_INTEGER:
395  // Write out the component.
396  p_end=sWriteCompressedName(p_temp,symbol_type,name);
397  break;
398 
399  default:
400  Dbg_MsgAssert(0,("Bad symbol_type"));
401  break;
402  }
403 
404  uint32 bytes_written_to_temp=p_end-p_temp;
405 
406  // Check that there is enough space before doing any writing.
407  if (bufferSize < bytes_written_to_temp)
408  {
409  return 0;
410  }
411 
412  uint8 *p_source=p_temp;
413  for (uint32 i=0; i<bytes_written_to_temp; ++i)
414  {
415  *p_buffer++=*p_source++;
416  }
417 
418  return p_buffer-p_buffer_before;
419 }

542  uint8 *p_buffer_before=p_buffer;
543 
544  // Check that there is enough space before doing any writing.
545  if (bufferSize<17)
546  {
547  return 0;
548  }
549

553  p_buffer=Write4Bytes(p_buffer,p_vector->mY);
554  p_buffer=Write4Bytes(p_buffer,p_vector->mZ);
555 
556  return p_buffer-p_buffer_before;
557 }

uint32 Script::WriteToBuffer ( CStruct *  p_structure,

626 {
627  Dbg_MsgAssert(p_buffer,("NULL p_buffer sent to WriteToBuffer"));
628  uint32 bytes_left=bufferSize;
629 
630  // Scan through the components adding each to the buffer.
631  CComponent *p_comp=NULL;
632  if (p_structure)
633  {
634  p_comp=p_structure->GetNextComponent(NULL);
635  }
636 
637  while (p_comp)
638  {
639  uint32 component_bytes_written=0;
640 
641  switch (p_comp->mType)
642  {
643  case ESYMBOLTYPE_INTEGER:
644  component_bytes_written=sIntegerWriteToBuffer(p_comp->mNameChecksum,p_comp->mIntegerValue,p_buffer,bytes_left);
645  break;
646 
647  case ESYMBOLTYPE_FLOAT:
648  component_bytes_written=sFloatWriteToBuffer(p_comp->mNameChecksum,p_comp->mFloatValue,p_buffer,bytes_left);
649  break;
650 
651  case ESYMBOLTYPE_NAME:
652  component_bytes_written=sChecksumWriteToBuffer(p_comp->mNameChecksum,p_comp->mChecksum,p_buffer,bytes_left);
653  break;
654 
655  case ESYMBOLTYPE_STRING:
656  component_bytes_written=sStringWriteToBuffer(p_comp->mNameChecksum,p_comp->mpString,p_buffer,bytes_left);
657  break;
658 
659  case ESYMBOLTYPE_LOCALSTRING:
660  component_bytes_written=sLocalStringWriteToBuffer(p_comp->mNameChecksum,p_comp->mpLocalString,p_buffer,bytes_left);
661  break;
662 
663  case ESYMBOLTYPE_PAIR:
664  component_bytes_written=sPairWriteToBuffer(p_comp->mNameChecksum,p_comp->mpPair,p_buffer,bytes_left);
665  break;
666 
667  case ESYMBOLTYPE_VECTOR:
668  component_bytes_written=sVectorWriteToBuffer(p_comp->mNameChecksum,p_comp->mpVector,p_buffer,bytes_left);
669  break;
670 
671  case ESYMBOLTYPE_STRUCTURE:
672  component_bytes_written=sStructureWriteToBuffer(p_comp->mNameChecksum,p_comp->mpStructure,p_buffer,bytes_left,assert);
673  break;
674 
675  case ESYMBOLTYPE_ARRAY:
676  component_bytes_written=sArrayWriteToBuffer(p_comp->mNameChecksum,p_comp->mpArray,p_buffer,bytes_left,assert);
677  break;
678 
679  case ESYMBOLTYPE_QSCRIPT:
680  component_bytes_written=sChecksumWriteToBuffer(p_comp->mNameChecksum,CRCD(0xb9c4f664,"InlineScript"),p_buffer,bytes_left);
681  break;
682 
683  default:
684  Dbg_MsgAssert(0,("Component type of '%s' is not supported in WriteToBuffer",GetTypeName(p_comp->mType)));
685  break;
686  }
687 
688  // If any of the above writes failed due to lack of space, then bail out too.
689  if (!component_bytes_written)
690  {
691  if (assert)
692  {
693  Dbg_MsgAssert(0,("WriteToBuffer: Buffer not big enough"));
694  }
695  return 0;
696  }
697 
698  bytes_left-=component_bytes_written;
699  p_buffer+=component_bytes_written;
700 
701  p_comp=p_structure->GetNextComponent(p_comp);
702  }
703 
704  // Add the terminating ESYMBOLTYPE_NONE
705  if (!bytes_left)
706  {
707  // Aargh! Not enough room left for the final byte!
708  if (assert)
709  {
710  Dbg_MsgAssert(0,("WriteToBuffer: Buffer not big enough"));
711  }
712  return 0;
713  }
714  *p_buffer++=ESYMBOLTYPE_NONE;
715  --bytes_left;
716 
717  // Return how many bytes got written.
718  return bufferSize-bytes_left;
719 }

◆ ReadFromBuffer() [1/2]

uint8 * Script::ReadFromBuffer ( CStruct *  p_structure,
uint8 *  p_buffer 
)

См. определение в файле utils.cpp строка 743

744 {
745  Dbg_MsgAssert(p_structure,("NULL p_structure"));
746  Dbg_MsgAssert(p_buffer,("NULL p_buffer sent to ReadFromBuffer"));
747  float zero_float=0.0f;
748 
749  // First clear anything currently in the structure.
750  p_structure->Clear();
751 
752  // Make sure we're using the script heap.
753  Mem::Manager::sHandle().PushContext(Mem::Manager::sHandle().ScriptHeap());
754 
755  // Scan through the buffer adding the components until ESYMBOLTYPE_NONE is reached.
756  while (true)
757  {
758  float x,y,z;
759  const char *p_string;
760  CStruct *p_struct;
761  CArray *p_array;
762 
763  // Get the type and the name checksum.
764  ESymbolType type=(ESymbolType)*p_buffer++;
765  if (type==ESYMBOLTYPE_NONE)
766  {
767  // All done.
768  break;
769  }
770 
771  // Get the name checksum, which may be stored as an index into a table of checksums
772  // to save space.
773  uint32 name=0;
774  if (type&MASK_8_BIT_NAME_LOOKUP)
775  {
776  Dbg_MsgAssert(!(type&MASK_16_BIT_NAME_LOOKUP),("Eh? Both lookup-table flags set ?"));
777 
778  #ifdef __PLAT_WN32__
779  // The lookup table is not loaded when compiling on PC
780  name=CRCD(0xef5f3f41,"CompressedName");
781  #else
782  CArray *p_table=GetArray(0x35115a20/*WriteToBuffer_CompressionLookupTable_8*/);
783  name=p_table->GetChecksum(*p_buffer);
784  #endif
785  ++p_buffer;
786  }
787  else if (type&MASK_16_BIT_NAME_LOOKUP)
788  {
789  #ifdef __PLAT_WN32__
790  name=CRCD(0xef5f3f41,"CompressedName");
791  #else
792  CArray *p_table=GetArray(0x25231f42/*WriteToBuffer_CompressionLookupTable_16*/);
793  name=p_table->GetChecksum(Read2Bytes(p_buffer).mUInt);
794  #endif
795  p_buffer+=2;
796  }
797  else
798  {
799  // It's not stored as an index, but as the full 4 byte checksum.
800  name=Read4Bytes(p_buffer).mChecksum;
801  p_buffer+=4;
802  }
803  type=(ESymbolType)( ((uint32)type) & ~(MASK_8_BIT_NAME_LOOKUP | MASK_16_BIT_NAME_LOOKUP) );
804 
805 
806  switch (type)
807  {
808  case ESYMBOLTYPE_INTEGER:
809  p_structure->AddInteger(name,Read4Bytes(p_buffer).mInt);
810  p_buffer+=4;
811  break;
812  case ESYMBOLTYPE_FLOAT:
813  p_structure->AddFloat(name,Read4Bytes(p_buffer).mFloat);
814  p_buffer+=4;
815  break;
816  case ESYMBOLTYPE_NAME:
817  p_structure->AddChecksum(name,Read4Bytes(p_buffer).mChecksum);
818  p_buffer+=4;
819  break;
820  case ESYMBOLTYPE_ZERO_FLOAT:
821  p_structure->AddFloat(name,zero_float);
822  break;
823  case ESYMBOLTYPE_ZERO_INTEGER:
824  p_structure->AddInteger(name,0);
825  break;
826  case ESYMBOLTYPE_INTEGER_ONE_BYTE:
827  p_structure->AddInteger(name,*(sint8*)p_buffer++);
828  break;
829  case ESYMBOLTYPE_UNSIGNED_INTEGER_ONE_BYTE:
830  p_structure->AddInteger(name,*p_buffer++);
831  break;
832  case ESYMBOLTYPE_INTEGER_TWO_BYTES:
833  p_structure->AddInteger(name,Read2Bytes(p_buffer).mInt);
834  p_buffer+=2;
835  break;
836  case ESYMBOLTYPE_UNSIGNED_INTEGER_TWO_BYTES:
837  p_structure->AddInteger(name,Read2Bytes(p_buffer).mUInt);
838  p_buffer+=2;
839  break;
840  case ESYMBOLTYPE_STRING:
841  p_string=(const char *)p_buffer;
842  p_structure->AddString(name,p_string);
843  p_buffer+=strlen(p_string);
844  ++p_buffer; // Skip over the terminator too.
845  break;
846  case ESYMBOLTYPE_LOCALSTRING:
847  p_string=(const char *)p_buffer;
848  p_structure->AddLocalString(name,p_string);
849  p_buffer+=strlen(p_string);
850  ++p_buffer; // Skip over the terminator too.
851  break;
852  case ESYMBOLTYPE_PAIR:
853  x=Read4Bytes(p_buffer).mFloat;
854  p_buffer+=4;
855  y=Read4Bytes(p_buffer).mFloat;
856  p_buffer+=4;
857  p_structure->AddPair(name,x,y);
858  break;
859  case ESYMBOLTYPE_VECTOR:
860  x=Read4Bytes(p_buffer).mFloat;
861  p_buffer+=4;
862  y=Read4Bytes(p_buffer).mFloat;
863  p_buffer+=4;
864  z=Read4Bytes(p_buffer).mFloat;
865  p_buffer+=4;
866  p_structure->AddVector(name,x,y,z);
867  break;
868  case ESYMBOLTYPE_STRUCTURE:
869  // Create a new structure, and fill it in by calling this function recursively.
870  p_struct=new CStruct;
871  p_buffer=ReadFromBuffer(p_struct,p_buffer);
872  // Add the new component.
873  p_structure->AddStructurePointer(name,p_struct);
874  break;
875  case ESYMBOLTYPE_ARRAY:
876  // Create a new array, and fill it in using the array's ReadFromBuffer.
877  p_array=new CArray;
878  p_buffer=ReadFromBuffer(p_array,p_buffer);
879  // Add the new component.
880  p_structure->AddArrayPointer(name,p_array);
881  break;
882  default:
883  Dbg_MsgAssert(0,("Unsupported component type of '%s' encountered in ReadFromBuffer",GetTypeName(type)));
884  break;
885  }
886  }
887 
888  Mem::Manager::sHandle().PopContext();
889 
890  return p_buffer;
891 }
